"],"variants":[{"name":"Reliford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  . Its bearers are mainly African Americans. Compare   Relaford  ,   Releford  ,   Relford  ."]},{"name":"Retherford","meanings":["Altered form of English   Rutherford  ."]}]},{"name":"Lorna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Invented by  R. D. Blackmore  for the heroine of his novel Lorna Doone (  1869 ), child captive of the outlawed Doones on Exmoor, who is eventually discovered to be in reality Lady Lorna Dugal, daughter of the Earl of Dugal. Blackmore seems to have derived the name from the Scottish place name <i>Lorn(e)</i> (Gaelic <i>Latharna</i>), a territory in Argyll."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lorna Rutherford was born in 1380, in West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland, her father, Sir Richard Rutherford of that ilk,, was 30 and her mother, Jean Douglas, was 35. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Baron Walter Turnbull - of Minto, Knight. She died in Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1380–":"1380–Surnud","1370–1401":"1370–1401","1370–1435":"1370–1435","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1380–1428":"1380–1428","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1412–1500":"1412–1500","1382–1440":"1382–1440","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1351–1425":"1351–1425","1346–1421":"1346–1421","1440":"1440","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1346":"1346","1500":"1500","1412":"1412","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1421":"1421","1454":"1454","1375":"1375","1428":"1428","West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland":"West Linton, Peeblesshire, Scotland","Lauder, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1380–":"1380–Kuollut","1370–1401":"1370–1401","1370–1435":"1370–1435","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1380–1428":"1380–1428","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1412–150